#week-title("One", "Reading Signatures & The Book of Nature")

=== Core Teaching

Every plant bears the mark of its nature visibly upon its body. The shape of its
leaves, the color of its flowers, the environment where it thrives, the time of
year it rises and falls — all of these are *signatures* written in the language of
nature. To read plant signatures is to begin reading the book of nature itself.

The *Golden Chain of Homer* establishes the philosophical basis: all things in
creation are "most closely chained together and interconnected." A deeply secret
connection pervades all of nature — one thing relates to the next, things depend
upon one another, and this connection appears as a continuous "up and down," a
movement back and forth between the volatile and the fixed. Nothing stands alone.

=== Topics This Week

- Reading plant signatures: form, colour, scent, habitat, season
- The philosophical basis of signatures in the _Golden Chain of Homer_
- Nature as a living language

#inner-work[
  *The Nature Vigil Deepened*

  Continue your daily vigil of nature with your chosen plant. This month, shift
  your focus to identifying its *signatures*. Observe its form, color, and scent
  with extreme detail. Record these in your journal.

  Based on these signatures, begin to speculate on which planetary force might
  govern this plant. Do not look it up in a book yet — trust your own developing
  perception.
]

